               <floruit notBefore="1508" notAfter="1549">He was an aristocrat of royal blood  who traced  his descent to <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                  <persName ref="PRS8595SayfaAr">Sayfa ʾArʿad</persName>. It was during the turbulent period of<roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS6229LebnaDe">Lǝbna Dǝngǝl</persName>, <persName ref="PRS3984Fanuel">Fānuʾel</persName> 
                  held the office of <roleName type="title">wāg šum </roleName>. He was among a few prominent warlords who were luck enough to survive during the onslaught led by  
                  <roleName type="title">ʾimām</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS1522Ahmadb">ʾAḥmad b. ʾIbrāhīm al-Ġāzī</persName>. 
                  He was also an important warlord during the reign of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                  <persName ref="PRS4428Galawdew">Galāwdewos</persName>.</floruit>   
                  <death when="1549"/>
